# ElevenLabs Voice Agent Standards

When creating or updating ElevenLabs conversational AI agents:

## 1. Language Code Normalization

**Always** use `getElevenLabsLanguageCode()` from `@/lib/voice-languages` when passing `language` to the ElevenLabs API. The API only accepts ISO 639-1 codes (en, fr, es, etc.). Values like `all`, `none`, `multilingual` from `VOICE_AGENT_LANGUAGES` must be normalized.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD - can pass invalid codes
language: user?.language || 'en'
language: updates.language || currentAgent.conversation_config?.agent?.language || 'en'

// ✅ GOOD
import { getElevenLabsLanguageCode } from '@/lib/voice-languages';
language: getElevenLabsLanguageCode(user?.language || 'en')
language: getElevenLabsLanguageCode(updates.language || currentAgent.conversation_config?.agent?.language || 'en')
```

## 2. API Route Timeout

API routes that create or provision ElevenLabs agents must set `maxDuration = 60` because agent creation/verification can take 30+ seconds and exceeds Vercel's default 30s limit.

```typescript
// Add to route files that call ElevenLabs convai/agents/create
export const maxDuration = 60;
```

Routes: crm-voice-agent, docpen/voice-agent, voice-agents (POST), voice-agents/[id]/auto-configure, industry-ai-employees/provision, real-estate/ai-employees/provision, professional-ai-employees/provision.

## 3. Turn Timeout (CRITICAL)

**Always** include `turn: { mode: 'turn', turn_timeout: 30 }` in `conversation_config` when creating or updating agents. When unset, ElevenLabs defaults to `turn_timeout: 7`, causing premature disconnect after 7 seconds of silence.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — agent defaults to 7s, disconnects quickly
conversation_config: { agent: {...}, conversation: {...} }

// ✅ GOOD — use TURN_CONFIG from @/lib/elevenlabs-constants
import { TURN_CONFIG } from '@/lib/elevenlabs-constants';
conversation_config: {
  turn: TURN_CONFIG,  // { mode: 'turn', turn_timeout: 30 }
  agent: {...},
  conversation: {...},
}
```

## 4. Per-Call Overrides

When building `voiceOverride.agent = { language: lang }` for workflow calls or dynamic variables, normalize the language:

```typescript
const { getElevenLabsLanguageCode } = await import('@/lib/voice-languages');
voiceOverride.agent = { language: getElevenLabsLanguageCode(lang) };
```

## 5. Shared Constants

Use `lib/elevenlabs-constants.ts` for `TURN_CONFIG` and `CONVERSATION_CONFIG` when patching agent timeouts.
